  "title": "Service Technician",
  "description": "<ul><li>Identification, maintenance and replacement of electronic equipment and computers.</li><li>Liaise with government agency on return and collection of faulty or repaired equipment.</li><li>Tracking and recording the fault patterns and trends for monthly progress reporting to government agency.</li><li>Provide guidance to general public on the use of on-site equipment such as Fee Collection Terminals.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Possess certificate in NITEC/Electrical/Electronic or related discipline</li><li>Able to work 12hrs rotating shifts (4 day work week)</li><li>Fresh ITE Graduates are welcome, training will be provided </li><li>Working location at Woodland & Tuas Checkpoints</li></ul>",
